6 B. Each sheriff may appoint as many reserve force deputy
7 sheriffs as are necessary to preserve the peace and dignity of the
8 county. A current list of each person holding such appointment
9 shall be maintained by the county sheriff and shall be available to
10 the public. Reserve force deputy sheriffs may perform duties which
11 encompass a particular act or a series of acts. The sheriff or a
12 Council on Law Enforcement Education and Training-certified deputy
13 sheriff shall accompany a reserve force deputy sheriff in the
14 performance of all duties assigned to such reserve force deputy
15 sheriff unless such reserve deputy has completed the required two-
16 hundred-forty-hour basic police course. Reserve force deputies may
17 receive compensation for their services. The sheriff may pay
18 reserve force deputies for travel expenses pursuant to the State
19 Travel Reimbursement Act. Such reserve deputy sheriffs shall
20 complete a two-hundred-forty-hour basic police course within six (6)
21 months after they have been commissioned to be paid by the county as
22 an individual reserve deputy. The sheriff may pay for additional
23 training courses attended by reserve force deputies.
