1 C. Reserve force deputy sheriffs shall not serve more than one
2 hundred forty (140) hours per calendar month.
3 D. The sheriff or a designee may deputize municipal police
4 officers subject to an interlocal governmental agreement to combine
5 city and county law enforcement efforts and to encourage cooperation
6 between city and county law enforcement officials. Liability for
7 the conduct of any municipal police officers deputized under the
8 terms and conditions of an interlocal governmental agreement shall
9 remain the responsibility of their municipal employer.
10 E. The sheriff may enter into mutual aid agreements pursuant to
11 the Interlocal Cooperation Act, Section 1002 et seq. of Title 74 of
12 the Oklahoma Statutes, to assist or provide law enforcement services
13 to any town, city, and county within this state and the sheriff and
14 deputies shall have law enforcement authority within the
15 jurisdiction making the request. The employing governmental unit
16 shall remain responsible for their officers or deputies pursuant to
17 any mutual aid agreement.
18 F. A sheriff of the county may respond to any request from any
19 other jurisdiction within the state for law enforcement assistance
20 in cases of emergency. The sheriff, deputy sheriffs, and reserve
21 deputy sheriffs serving in response to the emergency request shall
22 have the same powers and duties as though employed by the requesting
23 law enforcement agency, and when so acting they shall be deemed to
24 be acting within the scope of employment of the requesting law
