1 enfo rcement agency. Salaries, insurance, and other benefits shall
2 be provided in the regular manner by the county in which the
3 sheriff, deputy sheriffs, and reserve deputy sheriffs are regularly
4 employed. As used in this subsection, “emergency” means a sudden
5 and unforeseeable occurrence or condition, either as to its onset or
6 its extent, of such severity or magnitude that immediate response or
7 action is necessary to assist law enforcement agencies having
8 jurisdiction at the scene of the emergency to carry out their
9 functions.
10 G. A reserve force deputy sheriff shall be authorized to serve
11 civil process pursuant to Section 2004 of Title 12 of the Oklahoma
12 Statutes.
13 H. The sheriff may contract with a private security firm that
14 meets the requirements set forth in Sections 1750.1 through 1750.14
15 of Title 59 of the Oklahoma Statutes to guard any detainee or
16 prisoner temporarily housed for treatment in a medical facility
17 outside the confines of the jail. No private security firm may
18 transport a prisoner to or from an outside medical facility.
19 Transportation of a prisoner is only to be conducted by the sheriff
20 or deputy sheriff.
21 I. 1. Any sheriff of a county in which an event is occurring
22 and which the sheriff believes will require additional resources
23 than are normally available to the sheriff shall seek and submit
24 approval of a resolution to the board of county commissioners
