6 2. Any sheriff, deputy sheriff, or reserve deputy sheriff
7 assigned to work an event outside of his or her county of employment
8 shall have the same powers and duties as though employed by the
9 sheriff of the county in which the event takes place. Liability for
10 the conduct of any sheriff, deputy sheriff, or reserve deputy
11 sheriff, while in the performance of duties during such event or any
12 activity in conjunction with the event, shall remain the
13 responsibility of the employing county. Salaries, insurance, and
14 other benefits shall be provided in the regular manner by the county
15 in which the sheriff, deputy sheriff, or reserve deputy sheriff is
16 regularly employed.
17 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
